Review: Dude went from singing and dancing in Washington Heights, to using Pete Davidson’s dick as his weapon to take down a big unicorn. W.A.T.T.B.A.
What can’t this man accomplish? Time to put him in either the Sahara, the Amazon or the Congo. Or all of them and just make it a franchise called “Insert Location: Survival”
Nature is the most beautiful form of art in the world!!!

Started out really fun but petered out with over complex dialogue and explanation of what’s going on. Which of course is sorta needed in these but it felt just a bit too much. CGI was dope though, had me shouting at my tv

Felt the urge to watch another one of Green’s movies after Royal Hotel. Really loved this, one of those kind of stories where if you know, you know and if you don’t, you’re lucky. Big fan of stuff like this and Garner’s performance as well
Really wanted just a little bit more from this but still enjoyed it. Felt it coulda been a touch scarier and/or longer
Started really good but just petered out the further it went. Idk maybe was just cause the jokes were long ones that he’d linger on
